featured_reviews.review_id:
Jama Masjid Silao is an austere  mosque in Nalanda District. It des not follow Mughal arrhitecture. The mosque was constructed in 1741-42 by a father and son, Sayyid Muhammad and Sayyid Ghulam Najaf
It  is enclosed by high walls, not common in eastern India at that time.

On each of the exterior walls are inscriptions. The mosque's interior is sparsely ornamented. Cusped mihrabs and a more complex form of pendentives than seen before in Bihar are the sole decorative devices. Must visit while in Nalanda.
